         <div type="translation">
            <p><choice corresp="#a1"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">Welche Menschen da die Wälder verbrennen ...</seg><seg type="sec_transl" resp="TI">Whichever humans are burning the forests...</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>132</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a2"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">with foolish thinking</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a4"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">/// the beings will surely be reborn in the Raurāva hell, unless they turn away from there ...</seg></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">In der Raurava-Hölle werden die wesen sicherlich [wieder-]geboren werden, wenn sie nicht von dort umkehren.</seg><seg type="sec_transl" resp="TI">The beings will certainly be [re-]born in the Raurava-hell, if they do not turn back from there.</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>105</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a5"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:carling2000"/><citedRange>404</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a6"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:carling2000"/><citedRange>311</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:kolver1965"/><citedRange>24</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a7"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:hackstein1995"/><citedRange>175</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>84, 306, 310 n.2</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:kolver1965"/><citedRange>147</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">He will not drive off the causes if he does not protect himself against evil.</seg></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">He will not drive off the causes if he does not protect himself against evil.  (cf 306)</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:peyrot2013b"/><citedRange>248</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... wenn er sich nicht vor dem Bösen hütet.</seg><seg type="sec_transl" resp="TI">... if he does not beware of evil.</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>84</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a7 txt:m-a230#a8"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">Die Ursachen wird er nicht beseitigen, wenn er sich von dem Bösen nicht hütet.</seg><seg type="sec_transl" resp="TI">The causes he will not eliminate, if he does not beware of evil.</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>306, 310, fn. 2</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b1"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:knoll1996"/><citedRange>142</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b2"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1952"/><citedRange>19</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b3"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1970"/><citedRange>271</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">they will have obtained pleasure ..., and they will have driven off the seed of greed from their mind[s], ashamed and abashed they ... the evil ones ...</seg></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">they will have obtained pleasure …, and they will have driven off the seed of greed from their mind[s], ashamed and abashed they … the evil ones …</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:peyrot2013b"/><citedRange>621</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b4"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:carling2000"/><citedRange>341, 342</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>338 n.1</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">And what if they do evil according to the [spirit of] the times</seg></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">And what if they do evil according to the [spirit of] the times  (cf 342)</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:peyrot2013b"/><citedRange>632</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b5"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:meunier2013"/><citedRange>129, 141, 178, 179</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">Mais ils font le mal avec crainte, ils éprouvent du remords, ils confessent aussi.</seg></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">[Wenn] sie ... aber Böses (tun), [so] tun sie [es] mit Furcht, empfinden Reue [und] bekunden sie auch.</seg><seg type="sec_transl" resp="TI">[If] they ... to evil, however, they do [so] with fear, feel remorse [and] express it as well.</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>338, 348</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b6"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:hackstein1995"/><citedRange>306</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">(when) the Buddhas (rise) in the world, they [i.e. the beings] will indeed come together with them and will consequently be set free</seg></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">(Wenn sich) die Buddhas in der Welt (erheben), kommen sie [scil. die Wesen] sicherlich mit ihnen zusammen [und] werden alsdann erlöst.</seg><seg type="sec_transl" resp="TI">(When) the Buddhas arise in the world, they [i.e. the beings] will certainly meet with them [and] will then be redeemed.</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>475</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b7"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:sieg1916"/><citedRange>562</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1954"/><citedRange>726</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1957"/><citedRange>67</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">51. Accordingly, my spirit and thought concerning this kāvya opus/composition of a kāvya were directed toward the composition in Ārśi language in poetic form/according to the metre.</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b7 txt:m-a230#a1"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1957"/><citedRange>150</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice></p>
         </div>
